 immediate area, we sent the paladin and ranger north, south, and east to agro the other nearby mobs. As this new batch of mobs came into camp, the enchanters started to chain cast the Color Slant AoE Stun spells. We had about 10 mobs at this point. The 3 wizards then stepped away from the group and formed a rough triangle around the enchanters. The wizards turn to face inward and then cast Thunderclap. This has the effect of pushing all the mobs into a tight ball centering on the enchanters stunweb. All 3 wizards then step forward to be in range of all the mobs and started to chain cast Jylls AoE bomb spells. A minute later all the mobs were dead. Total damage taken by 8 people doing this was approx 3 bubbles between us. Everyone then sat to meditate and once FM we repeated the process to clear any other mobs that were in range of the Portal. After that we moved north and repeated the bombing several times. Eventually we used this method to pull and kill the entire Temple of Amy's and Ambnesia was able to loot her Shissar for an Epic piece. We did have 1 wipeout, mainly due to late adds that were not grouped into the stun web properly. It was a very ez CR tho since we had cleared all the mobs on the West side of zone. <br><br>With a raid present, using these tactics, it will be very ez to clear the entire Fear plane in under 2 hours.<br><br>Now for a couple points that would apply during a full guild raid.<br>1. Zone Breakin will be accomplished with 3 Wizzies, 2 Enchanters, and 1 cleric. There is no need for more than that to clear the entry area. If any problems occur during initial entry, any 1 of the wizzies can cast (Group TL to bind or Evac) and the party will land at the Fear Portal ready to try again.<br><br>2. Once the full raid is in zone- It is very important that everyone stay BEHIND the AoE group. The pullers must bring the mobs into the Stunweb for ez grouping and bombing. If any guildies are not in correct position BEHIND the AoE groups then the mobs may agro and spread out and this can cause many problems. Once ALL the mobs have been pulled into the stun web, I will shout for Bombs and everyone else can then move in to help kill. The rest of the raid groups should concentrate on any mobs that are on the outside of the stunweb..and should try to push mobs in toward the enchanters.<br><br>3. With more firepower than 3 wizards available to bomb or help kill monsters, we will be killing a very large number of mobs very quickly. There will be very little downtime needed for medding. <br><br>4.Communication and Coordination are critical for AoE tactics to work. It takes alot of practice and trust to learn to AoE effectively. Over the past few months I have been practicing with and training guild members in this tactic. It is expected that everyone pay attention and respond quickly to requests from raid leaders. I should not have to mention the danger involved when pulling 20 to 30 Fear Mobs at a time. Like any plane raid, 1 person that does not follow directions or wanders off can kill the raid.<br><br>5. LAG is DEATH. AoE bombing is fast and alot of fun..BUT..it also can create insane lag. Everyone should use full raid settings to minimize lag on their systems. Otherwise when i call for Bombs we will see many many shouts of &quot;insert name here-Linkdead&quot;. A list of suggested graphics settings will be communicated before the raid starts.<br><br>6. 30 dead mobs at a time means the possibility of 30 Fear Armor or item drops at a time. Please be patient and cooperative with raid leaders and communicate item drops with them. We will have to be quick to get all the loots distributed before they poof..... heh, I never thought the prospect of getting too many planar armor drops would be a problem.<br><br>7. Monks get to take a well deserved rest from pulling with this strategy. We want pullers to be fast and tough so they can survive big train pulls and FD is not a need skill. Paladins are ideal for this due to combination of high AC and HP, in addition to DA and LoH abilities. These make surviving multiple Harm Touches from Amys in the Temple a more survivable experience. So all you guild Paladins go print up a Fear map and study it....yer not gonna be asked to pull many other times or places, so have fun with it while you can... <br><br>8. If you have a group of people that are NOT experienced at AoE tactics...I strongly recommend finding a zone to practice these steps in. Maidens Eye works well for this...many many mobs, adds to deal with, etc. Take your AoE group here to practice and learn communication, coordination, and timing before trying Fear.<br><br>This strategy makes Fear Entry and clearing a very simple task. <br><br>Aumadar &lt;the mad bomber&gt; Arkanum  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=boum>Boum</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/7/02 6:59:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm21.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=182.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A post I made to my guild recently regarding Fear AoE ta</span><hr size=1> Thanks a lot one all the details. I'll start training all the mages and druids in guild to aoe tactics very soon so we're ready for that Fear clearing party soon <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usilverbladetheenchanter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Silverblade the Enchanter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font co